SIMPLE: inhume
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inhume
<hw>In*hume"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Inhumed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inhuming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>inhumer</ets>. See
<er>Inhumate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To deposit, as a dead body, in the earth; to bury;
to inter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Weeping they bear the mangled heaps of slain,⟦br⟧
<qex>Inhume</qex> the natives in their native plain.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bury or place in warm earth for chemical or
medicinal purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
